  "content": " <div data-elementor-type=\"wp-post\" data-elementor-id=\"8948\" class=\"elementor elementor-8948\" data-elementor-settings=\"{&quot;ha_cmc_init_switcher&quot;:&quot;no&quot;}\"> <section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-8e96df2 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"8e96df2\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-e-type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_ha_eqh_enable&quot;:false}\"> <div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\"> <div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-4fab26f\" data-id=\"4fab26f\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-e-type=\"column\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\"> <div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b79c300 elementor-widget elementor-widget-html\" data-id=\"b79c300\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"html.default\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-container\"> <script async src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-5767364969818632\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"></script> <ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" style=\"display:block; text-align:center;\" data-ad-layout=\"in-article\" data-ad-format=\"fluid\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-5767364969818632\" data-ad-slot=\"6261327459\"></ins>  </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </section> <section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-37e1060 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"37e1060\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-e-type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_ha_eqh_enable&quot;:false}\"> <div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\"> <div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-76697c6\" data-id=\"76697c6\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-e-type=\"column\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\"> <div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a16e9ad elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"a16e9ad\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-container\"> <h2 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 15pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ead1dc; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; -webkit-text-decoration-skip: none; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">POLYMENORRHOEA/ EPIMENORRHOEA</span></h2><blockquote style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 19pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #fff2cc; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Polymenorrhea</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">, also known as </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #fff2cc; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">epimenorrhoea</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">, is a medical condition characterized by</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> frequent menstrual periods that occur more frequently than the normal menstrual cycle</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">. </span></blockquote><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 19pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #fff2cc; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Polymenorrhoea </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">also refers to </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">menstruation periods that occur at shorter intervals than usual (14-21 days), but they are frequent and regular.</span></p> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </section> <section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-2c95994 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"2c95994\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-e-type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_ha_eqh_enable&quot;:false}\"> <div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\"> <div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-62f940e\" data-id=\"62f940e\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-e-type=\"column\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\"> <div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-336bcaf elementor-widget elementor-widget-html\" data-id=\"336bcaf\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"html.default\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-container\"> <script async src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-5767364969818632\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"></script> <ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" style=\"display:block; text-align:center;\" data-ad-layout=\"in-article\" data-ad-format=\"fluid\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-5767364969818632\" data-ad-slot=\"6261327459\"></ins>  </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </section> <section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-e1b80d2 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"e1b80d2\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-e-type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_ha_eqh_enable&quot;:false}\"> <div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\"> <div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-9c01b07\" data-id=\"9c01b07\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-e-type=\"column\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\"> <div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-1ba074b elementor-widget elementor-widget-image\" data-id=\"1ba074b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-container\"> <img decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"365\" src=\"/images/POLYMENORRHOEA-EPIMENORRHOEA-1-e1705297969172.png\" class=\"attachment-large size-large wp-image-8951\" alt=\"Signs and Symptoms of Polymenorrhea/Epimenorrhoea: Menstrual Cycles Shorter than 21 Days: Defined by the duration between the onset of one period and the beginning of the next, with cycles constantly falling below the normal 21-days. Frequent Menstrual Periods: Menstrual bleeding occurring every two weeks or at intervals of less than 14 days, indicating increased frequency compared to the standard monthly cycle. Altered Bleeding Patterns: Variations in blood flow, with episodes of lighter or heavier bleeding than what is considered for the individual. Increased Menstrual Discomfort: Discomfort or pain associated with menstruation, more than the discomfort experienced during a regular menstrual cycle. Fatigue or Tiredness: Resulting from more frequent blood loss due to polymenorrhea, leading to a decrease in energy levels and an increased sense of tiredness. Emotional and Psychological Impact: Potential emotional consequences, including anxiety or mood swings, from the physical and hormonal changes associated with more frequent menstrual cycles.\" srcset=\"/images/POLYMENORRHOEA-EPIMENORRHOEA-1-e1705297969172.png 1024w, https://nursesrevisionuganda.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/POLYMENORRHOEA-EPIMENORRHOEA-1-e1705297969172-600x214.png 600w, https://nursesrevisionuganda.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/POLYMENORRHOEA-EPIMENORRHOEA-1-e1705297969172-300x107.png 300w, https://nursesrevisionuganda.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/POLYMENORRHOEA-EPIMENORRHOEA-1-e1705297969172-768x274.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /> </div> </div> <div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-9111bdc elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"9111bdc\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-container\"> <h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 19pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ead1dc; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; -webkit-text-decoration-skip: none; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Causes of Polymenorrhea/Epimenorrhoea:</span></h4><ol><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Hormonal imbalances</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">: Fluctuations in oestrogen and progesterone levels can disrupt the normal menstrual cycle and result in more frequent periods.</span></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Thyroid disorders</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Overactive thyroid (hyperthyroidism) or underactive thyroid (hypothyroidism) can affect hormone production and menstrual regularity.</span></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Polycystic ovary syndrome</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> (PCOS): This condition is characterized by hormonal imbalances, enlarged ovaries with cysts, and irregular menstrual cycles.</span></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Uterine abnormalities</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">: Conditions such as uterine fibroids, polyps, or adenomyosis can cause abnormal bleeding and frequent periods.</span></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Stress and lifestyle factors</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">: Chronic stress, excessive exercise, drastic weight changes, and poor nutrition can disrupt the hormonal balance and contribute to polymenorrhea.</span></li></ol> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </section> <section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-d126485 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"d126485\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-e-type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_ha_eqh_enable&quot;:false}\"> <div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\"> <div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-edf2fea\" data-id=\"edf2fea\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-e-type=\"column\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\"> <div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b41d5ed elementor-widget elementor-widget-html\" data-id=\"b41d5ed\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"html.default\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-container\"> <script async src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-5767364969818632\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"></script>  <ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" style=\"display:block\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-5767364969818632\" data-ad-slot=\"7570414357\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\"></ins>  </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </section> <section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-943f8ae elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"943f8ae\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-e-type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_ha_eqh_enable&quot;:false}\"> <div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\"> <div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-bfc012f\" data-id=\"bfc012f\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-e-type=\"column\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\"> <div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2cceeb0 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"2cceeb0\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-container\"> <h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 15pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ead1dc; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; -webkit-text-decoration-skip: none; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Signs and Symptoms of Polymenorrhea/Epimenorrhoea:</span></h4><ul><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Menstrual Cycles Shorter than 21 Days</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">: Defined by the duration between the onset of one period and the beginning of the next, with cycles constantly falling below the normal 21-days.</span></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Frequent Menstrual Periods</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">: Menstrual bleeding occurring every two weeks or at intervals of less than 14 days, indicating increased frequency compared to the standard monthly cycle.</span></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Altered Bleeding Patterns</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">: Variations in blood flow, with episodes of lighter or heavier bleeding than what is considered for the individual.</span></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Increased Menstrual Discomfort</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">: Discomfort or pain associated with menstruation, more than the discomfort experienced during a regular menstrual cycle.</span></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Fatigue or Tiredness</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">: Resulting from more frequent blood loss due to polymenorrhea, leading to a decrease in energy levels and an increased sense of tiredness.</span></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Emotional and Psychological Impact</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">: Potential emotional consequences, including anxiety or mood swings, from the physical and hormonal changes associated with more frequent menstrual cycles.</span></li></ul> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </section> <section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-a4fb4b4 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"a4fb4b4\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-e-type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_ha_eqh_enable&quot;:false}\"> <div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\"> <div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-84bac32\" data-id=\"84bac32\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-e-type=\"column\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\"> <div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-2c1929b elementor-widget elementor-widget-html\" data-id=\"2c1929b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"html.default\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-container\"> <script async src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-5767364969818632\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"></script> <ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" style=\"display:block; text-align:center;\" data-ad-layout=\"in-article\" data-ad-format=\"fluid\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-5767364969818632\" data-ad-slot=\"6261327459\"></ins>  </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </section> <section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-9f0c461 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"9f0c461\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-e-type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_ha_eqh_enable&quot;:false}\"> <div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\"> <div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-fbc0449\" data-id=\"fbc0449\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-e-type=\"column\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\"> <div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b0014fd elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"b0014fd\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-container\"> <h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 15pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ead1dc; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; -webkit-text-decoration-skip: none; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Investigations for Polymenorrhea/Epimenorrhoea:</span></h4><ol><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Medical history and physical examination</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> A thorough evaluation of the menstrual patterns, symptoms, and any underlying medical conditions is conducted. A pelvic examination may be performed to assess the reproductive organs.</span></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Hormone level assessment:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Blood tests may be done to measure hormone levels, including oestrogen, progesterone, thyroid hormones, and other relevant hormones.</span></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Pelvic ultrasound:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> This imaging test can provide visual information about the ovaries, uterus, and any structural abnormalities.</span></li><li><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-af703465-7fff-199a-c32e-8ab166c44005\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-style: italic; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">Endometrial biopsy</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; color: #000000; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\">: A sample of the uterine lining may be obtained and examined to rule out any abnormalities or cancer.</span></span></li></ol> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </section> <section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-b894432 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"b894432\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-e-type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_ha_eqh_enable&quot;:false}\"> <div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\"> <div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-1d1e007\" data-id=\"1d1e007\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-e-type=\"column\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\"> <div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-06925f4 elementor-widget elementor-widget-html\" data-id=\"06925f4\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"html.default\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-container\"> <script async src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-5767364969818632\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"></script> <ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" style=\"display:block\" data-ad-format=\"fluid\" data-ad-layout-key=\"-6q+ef+1v-2m-h\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-5767364969818632\" data-ad-slot=\"2010257102\"></ins>  </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </section> <section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-6d43173 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"6d43173\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-e-type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_ha_eqh_enable&quot;:false}\"> <div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\"> <div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-d144089\" data-id=\"d144089\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-e-type=\"column\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\"> <div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b8a6152 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"b8a6152\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-container\"> <h4 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 15pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ead1dc; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; -webkit-text-decoration-skip: none; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Medical and Nursing Management of Polymenorrhea/Epimenorrhoea:</span></h4><ol><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Hormonal therapy</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">: Depending on the underlying cause, hormonal medications, such as oral contraceptives or hormone-regulating medications, may be prescribed to regulate the menstrual cycle and reduce the frequency of periods.</span></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Treatment of underlying conditions</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">: If polymenorrhea is caused by conditions such as PCOS or uterine abnormalities, appropriate treatment strategies will be implemented to address the specific cause. Carry out dilatation and curettage (D&amp;C) to remove retained products if its the cause.</span></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Lifestyle modifications</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Stress reduction techniques, maintaining a balanced diet, regular exercise, and adequate sleep can help regulate hormonal balance and promote overall well-being.</span></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Supportive care</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">: Nursing management focuses on providing emotional support, educating patients about menstrual hygiene, symptom management, and lifestyle modifications.</span></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.38;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #d9ead3; font-weight: 400; font-style: italic; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Monitoring and follow-up</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Poppins,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">: Monitoring patients\u2019 response to treatment, assessing the effectiveness of interventions, and ensuring appropriate follow-up care should be put into considerations.</span></li></ol> </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </section> <section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-c8fe9e0 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"c8fe9e0\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-e-type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;_ha_eqh_enable&quot;:false}\"> <div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\"> <div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-ab1a290\" data-id=\"ab1a290\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-e-type=\"column\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\"> <div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-33d5816 elementor-widget elementor-widget-html\" data-id=\"33d5816\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"html.default\"> <div class=\"elementor-widget-container\"> <script async src=\"https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js?client=ca-pub-5767364969818632\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"></script> <ins class=\"adsbygoogle\" style=\"display:block\" data-ad-format=\"autorelaxed\" data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-5767364969818632\" data-ad-slot=\"1271890507\"></ins>  </div> </div> </div> </div> </div> </section> </div> <!-- .entry-content .clear --> ",
  "semester": "year-1-semester-1"
